•’Щ@005cecae8ffc5d3872fbfcfb15e598e15d26bf988c7f12fb9ba10cadc56d009eЩ„Title: title: polars concat-str
Path: expression
Content:









``polars concat-str``
[link: /commands/categories/expression.md] ’Щ@f7ab0d8267773f4ce7dc344ce76d549e4b37ea9d5abd952736718cd4d26a2b7bЩzTitle: title: polars concat-str
Path: Signature
Content:
``> polars concat-str {flags} (separator) (concat expressions)``
’Щ@cb55819120c81c1de53c0df11b70811d491743231ef7295f76f38d3c7013f138ЩАTitle: title: polars concat-str
Path: Parameters
Content:
``separator``
: Separator used during the concatenation.
``concat expressions``
: Expression(s) that define the string concatenation.
’Щ@b4e1787c8e12d3ac9e62249d4b30d290fa5691b5635c082747863d4809e8f9eeЩfTitle: title: polars concat-str
Path: Input/output types:
Content:
input
output
any
polars_expression
’Щ@4ee727776ff7d70d5c243623ea80c2ab495597cf0a3af028f4ab9cbf56711736Ъ=Title: title: polars concat-str
Path: Examples
Content:
Creates a concat string expression
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> let df = ([[a b c]; [one two 1] [three four 2]] | polars into-df);
    $df | polars with-column ((polars concat-str "-" [(polars col a) (polars col b) ((polars col c) * 2)]) | polars as concat)
